        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-28 12:54:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHere is whats was happening\n1) using the following two sed commands we would set the nodePorts\n  sed -i-- 's/nodePort: [0-9]\\{2\\}[02468]\\{1\\}/nodePort: '\"$4\"'/g' $3/all-services.yaml\n  sed -i-- 's/nodePort: [0-9]\\{2\\}[13579]\\{1\\}/nodePort: '\"$5\"'/g' $3/all-services.yaml\n2) deploy service using the updated service file.\nkubectl --namespace $1-$2 create -f ../$2/all-services.yaml\n\n3) Revert back what we did using sed (back to clean state)\n  mv $3/all-services.yaml-- $3/all-services.yaml\n\nWith you change you don't have step 2, so what is being done using sed is useless because you just overwrite what did using sed and didn't make use of it yet.\n\nIs anyone testing any of these? it would been easily caught.\n\nAlso commit message is misleading you are not adding support for multi instance. it was there before you are fixing what got broken by a previous patch.\n\n > (1 comment)\n\nHi Munir,\n\nCould you explain what you meant by your comment?\nThis was the original order of the lines.\nSed edited all-services, no \"all-services.yaml--\" was created but the mv line was still there.\nAccording to your previous comment I added the line, but I think I'm missing the purpose.\n\nThanks!\nKeren",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "6864d7942da5de6c9331b21c2451b1a6cf7f0575",
        "author": {
