        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-28 13:48:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nmulti ONAP instances didn't work in the last revert when using the same namespace, since there can't be services with the same names in the same namespace.\nfor this reason we tested with different namespaces as we thought your intent was.\nI fixed the location on the mv line, so previous version is saved. and you are right - this is a fix to support the broken multi onap envs (with different namespaces).\nIn order for multi-ONAP to be able to load with the same namespaces, a new ticket should be opened, since it will require the parametrization of the service names and therefor all DNS resolutions.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
